headline: Does Amphenol's (APH) $7.5B Debt Raise and Dividend Hike Mark a New Capital Strategy?
summary: Amphenol Corporation recently announced the completion of a multi-tranche senior notes offering totaling US$7.5 billion, with maturities ranging from 2027 to 2055 and both fixed and floating rate structures. The company stated that proceeds will be used to fund its acquisition of CommScope’s Connectivity and Cable Solutions businesses and for general corporate purposes. An increase in the quarterly dividend by 52% further signals Amphenol's confidence in its earnings power and cash flow,...
